                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-02">
                    <head>2 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-02"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor>
                        <subject>Smithsonian Institution</subject>
                    </bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="555"/>
                        <dateline>February 1839.</dateline>
                        <p><date>2. V:30.</date> Saturday</p>
                        <p>Call at the Bank of Washington. Meeting of joint Smithson Committee—
                            Present <persRef ref="robbins-asher">Robbins</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="benton-thomas">Benton</persRef>, <persRef ref="southard-samuel"
                                >Southard</persRef>, <persRef ref="preston-william2"
                                >Preston</persRef>, <persRef ref="bayard-richard"
                            >Bayard</persRef></p>
                        <p>Adams, <persRef ref="garland-james">Garland</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="shepard-charles">Shepard</persRef>, <persRef ref="ogle-charles"
                                >Og</persRef></p>


                    </div>
                </div>
                <pb n="556" type="ms"/>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-04">
                    <head>4 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-04"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="557" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>Monday 4 Feb<hi rend="superscript">y</hi> 1839—</date></p>
                        <list>
                            <head>Bills</head>
                            <item>N. 152 For the relief of the Heirs of <persRef
                                    ref="sampson-crocker">Crocker Sampson</persRef></item>
                            <item>307. Relief of the Representatives of <persRef
                                    ref="tudor-william2">William Tudor jun<hi rend="superscript"
                                        >r</hi></persRef></item>
                            <item>366. Relief of <persRef ref="lobdell-ebenezer">Ebenezer
                                    Lobdell</persRef></item>
                            <item>1051. Relief of the Representatives of <persRef ref="huddy-joshua"
                                    >Joshua Huddy</persRef>—</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-05">
                    <head>5 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-05"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <p><date>5 Feb<hi rend="superscript">y.</hi></date>
                            <persRef ref="borland-alexander">Alex<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                Borland</persRef>, <persRef ref="cornwell-joseph">D<hi
                                    rend="superscript">r</hi> Joseph B. Cornwell</persRef>—</p>
                        <p><persRef ref="loring-thomas2">Thomas Loring’s</persRef> Letter.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-06">
                    <head>6 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-06"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor>
                        <subject>Recreation</subject>
                        <subject>Smithsonian Institution</subject>
                    </bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <p><date>Wednesday 6. Feb<hi rend="superscript">y</hi>—</date> Meeting of
                            the joint Smithson Committee— I offered 5 Resolutions against the
                            appropriation of any part of the fund to any institute of education—very
                            little discussed— <persRef ref="robbins-asher">M<hi rend="superscript"
                                    >r</hi> Robbins</persRef> is to report a Bill constituting a
                            board of Trustees on Commission to report a plan for the application of
                            the fund, to the next Congress— H.R.U.S— <persRef ref="haynes-charles"
                                >Haynes</persRef> moved again a suspension of the rules to offer a
                            Resolution to discharge the Committee of the whole on the Union, from
                            the <persRef ref="vanburen-martin">President’s</persRef> Message, to
                            take it up in the House—lost<space/>to<space/>not two thirds— Reports
                            from Committees received— Orders of the day— Army Appropriation Bill
                            amendment of a Section appropriating 30000 dollars <pb n="558" type="ms"
                            />for surveys— <persRef ref="pickens-francis">Pickens</persRef>,
                            <persRef ref="robertson-john2">Robertson</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="cambreleng-churchill">Cambreleng</persRef> against it— <persRef
                                ref="mercer-charles">Mercer</persRef> for it— Adjourned after 4.</p>
                        <p><persRef ref="campbell-archibald">Campbell</persRef> dined with us—
                            Evening whist.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-07">
                    <head>7 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-07"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <p><date>7. V. Thursday—</date> Day for the Meeting of the Committee of
                            Manufactures— I alone there— H.R.U.S—</p>
                        <p><persRef ref="johnson-william2">W. Cost Johnson</persRef> reported from
                            the great Land Committee of 26. asking to be discharged from the subject
                            referred to them; and no further action of the House. Robertson offers
                            sundry Resolutions as Amendments to the Reports—and speaks till the call
                            of the Orders of the day.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-08">
                    <head>8 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-08"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="559" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>8. V. Friday—</date> Meeting of the Massachusetts
                                Delegation—<persRef ref="davis-john4">J. Davis</persRef>—Adams,
                                <persRef ref="borden-nathaniel">Borden</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="briggs-george">Briggs</persRef>, <persRef ref="calhoun-william"
                                >Calhoun</persRef>, <persRef ref="cushing-caleb">Cushing</persRef>,
                                <persRef ref="fletcher-richard">Fletcher</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="grennell-george">Grennell</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="hastings-william">Hastings</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="parmenter-william">Parmenter</persRef>
                            <persRef ref="reed-john">Reed</persRef>— M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                            Fletcher said <persRef ref="thayer-minot">Col<hi rend="superscript"
                                    >l.</hi> Thayer</persRef> had seen the <persRef
                                ref="poinsett-joel">Secretary of War</persRef>, who would recommend
                            an appropriation of 65000 dollars for fortifications in Boston Harbour.
                            I was charged to see <persRef ref="cambreleng-churchill"
                                >Cambreleng</persRef> and arrange with him, the manner of
                            introducing it— I saw him— He said <persRef ref="wright-silas"
                                >Wright</persRef> would introduce it as an amendment in the army
                            Bill, passed the House yesterday— H.R.U.S. <persRef ref="robertson-john2"
                                >Robertson</persRef> continued his Speech on his Resolutions offered
                            as an Amendment to <persRef ref="johnson-william2">W. Cost
                                Johnson’s</persRef> Report of the great Land Committee of 26—
                                <persRef ref="yell-archibald">Yell</persRef> offered an Amendment to
                            the Amendment.— Orders of the day— Private Bills— Sundry passed—others
                            rejected. Reconsiderations moved— Notice from <persRef
                                ref="robbins-asher">A. Robbins</persRef> postponing till Wednesday
                            the next meeting of the Smithson Com<hi rend="superscript">ee</hi>—and I
                            notified the members of the Com<hi rend="superscript">ee.</hi> of
                            Manufactures</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-09">
                    <head>9 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-09"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="560" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>9. V:30.</date> Saturday</p>
                        <p>Com<hi rend="superscript">ee.</hi> of Manufactures.</p>
                        <p>Adams, <persRef ref="naylor-charles">Naylor</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="slade-william">Slade</persRef>, <persRef ref="kennedy-john"
                                >Kennedy</persRef>, <persRef ref="tillinghast-joseph"
                                >Tillinghast</persRef>, <persRef ref="elmore-franklin"
                                >Elmore</persRef>. Absent <persRef ref="biddle-richard"
                                >Biddle</persRef>, <persRef ref="hunter-robert">Hunter</persRef>
                            <persRef ref="vail-henry">Vail</persRef>.</p>
                        <p>Senate Bill N. 224 to be reported to the House, with an Amendment—a 3<hi
                                rend="superscript">d.</hi> Section to refund duties paid on Railroad
                            fastenings— The Letter from W<space/>to <persRef ref="howard-bf">B. F.
                                Howard</persRef> praying for a repeal of the duty on Cotton—3 cents
                            a pound, laid on the table</p>
                        <p>Elmore says he has no objection to the Bill.</p>
                        <p>Petition of <persRef ref="annable-td">T. D. Annable</persRef> and others
                            for a duty on Starch</p>
                        <p>To move discharge of the Com<hi rend="superscript">ee</hi> and reference
                            to the Comm<hi rend="superscript">ee.</hi> of the whole on the Union
                            upon the Bill— Pet<hi rend="superscript">n</hi> for a duty on ready made
                            Sails, laid on the table—</p>
                        <p>H.R.U.S— <persRef ref="robertson-john2">Robertson</persRef>, continues
                            his Speech, on his Resolutions concerning the Public Lands— Orders of
                            the Day— Private business— <persRef ref="rumsey-james"
                                >Rumsey’s</persRef> beautiful Speech— I reported Senate Bill 224
                            with the additional Section—</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-10">
                    <head>10 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-10"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor>
                        <subject>Anti-Slavery Petitions to Congress</subject>
                    </bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="561" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>10. VI. Sunday—</date> Heard <persRef ref="fowler-philemon"
                                >Fowler</persRef> from Joshua 7.1 <persRef ref="achan"
                                >Achan</persRef> and the accursed thing.— <persRef
                                ref="campbell-archibald">Campbell</persRef> at dinner. S<hi
                                rend="superscript">t.</hi> John’s P.M— <persRef ref="hawley-william"
                                >Hawley</persRef> read prayers for Quinquagesima Sunday— Stranger
                            preached from Psalm 104–29–30. apostrophe to some of the auditory—
                                <persRef ref="smith-catherine-johnson">M<hi rend="superscript"
                                    >rs</hi> Smith</persRef> dined at <persRef
                                ref="johnson-thomas-baker">her brother’s</persRef>— Campbell and
                                <persRef ref="u">Harry</persRef> here this Evening—bullying Letters—
                            Abolition Petitions.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-11">
                    <head>11 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-11"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <p><date>11. VI.</date> Monday—H.R.U.S. Resolution day, <persRef
                                ref="haynes-charles">Haynes</persRef> moves to suspend the Rules to
                            move to discharge the Com<hi rend="superscript">ee</hi> of the whole on
                            the Union from the further consideration of the <persRef
                                ref="vanburen-martin">President’s</persRef> Message—Lost. <persRef
                                ref="bronson-isaac">Bronson</persRef> moves to go at once into the
                            business of the Territories—lost— Res<hi rend="superscript">ns.</hi>
                            called beginning with Ioway— Sandstone Resolution— <persRef
                                ref="pratt-zadock">Pratt</persRef>
                            <persRef ref="taliaferro-john">Taliaferro</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="naylor-charles">Naylor</persRef>
                            <persRef ref="lincoln-levi2">Lincoln</persRef> &amp;c— Com<hi
                                rend="superscript">ee:</hi> on public buildings to enquire— <persRef
                                ref="slade-william">Slade’s</persRef> Resolution about men in
                            chains—flurry— My Resolution to amend the 18<hi rend="superscript"
                                >th.</hi> Rule about Petitions lies over one day— After 2. Orders of
                            the day Territorial Bills.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-12">
                    <head>12 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-12"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="562" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>12. V:30.</date> Tuesday— H.R.U.S— Territorial Bills, in Committee
                            of the whole on the Union. <persRef ref="pickens-francis"
                                >Pickens</persRef> in the Chair— He decides that a Bill, for selling
                            public Lands to the Alabama, Florida, and Georgia Railroad Company is
                            not a territorial Bill of those specially assigned for this day— Appeal
                            from his decision—confirmed by the Committee— Other Bills passed—</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-15">
                    <head>15 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-15"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor>
                        <subject>Smithsonian Institution</subject>
                        <subject>Anti-Slavery Petitions to Congress</subject>
                    </bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="563" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>15. VI.</date> Friday— Smithsonian Com<hi rend="superscript"
                                >ee</hi>—<persRef ref="robbins-asher">Robbins</persRef>—<persRef
                                ref="garland-james">Garland</persRef>. Robbins printed reasons,
                            which he never offered, and was not authorised by the Committee to have
                            printed. He said he was authorized by the Committee of the Senate to
                            Report his Bill</p>
                        <p>H.R.U.S— The Land Committee Resolution and <persRef ref="robertson-john2"
                                >Robertson’s</persRef> Resolutions— <persRef ref="harrison-albert"
                                >Harrison</persRef> of Missouri—refuses to yield the floor to
                                <persRef ref="petrikin-david">Petrikin</persRef>. His Speech.</p>
                        <p><persRef ref="cushing-caleb">Cushing</persRef> brought me a Letter from
                                <persRef ref="kingsbury-fisher">F. A. Kingsbury</persRef>—and 4
                            Petitions from Weymouth.</p>
                        <table>
                            <row>
                                <cell role="name"><persRef ref="richards-elias">Richards</persRef>
                                    Elias</cell>
                                <cell role="num">1.</cell>
                                <cell role="num">2.</cell>
                                <cell role="num">3.</cell>
                                <cell role="num">6.</cell>
                                <cell role="num">95.</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell role="name">Same</cell>
                                <cell role="num"/>
                                <cell role="num">4.</cell>
                                <cell role="num">5.</cell>
                                <cell role="num">6</cell>
                                <cell role="num">54.</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell role="name">Same</cell>
                                <cell role="num"/>
                                <cell role="num"/>
                                <cell role="num"/>
                                <cell role="num">7</cell>
                                <cell role="num">56</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell role="name"><persRef ref="damon-zachariah">Damon
                                        Zachariah</persRef></cell>
                                <cell role="num"/>
                                <cell role="num"/>
                                <cell role="num"/>
                                <cell role="num">8.</cell>
                                <cell role="num">140.</cell>
                            </row>
                        </table>

                    </div>
                </div>
                <pb n="564" type="ms"/>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-18">
                    <head>18 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-18"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="565" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>18. V.</date> Monday— H.R.U.S. Petitions, all received and laid on
                            the Table— No call of the States— Rules suspended—yeas and nays refused
                                25—ag<hi rend="superscript">t.</hi> suspension 49— Order of the
                            House— Debate on <persRef ref="robertson-john2">Robertson’s</persRef>
                            Resolutions <persRef ref="harrison-albert">Harrison</persRef> concludes—
                            Treasury Note Bill passed 114 to 88. Dinner at <persRef
                                ref="bodisko-alexander">Bodisco’s</persRef>—Adams, <persRef
                                ref="bayard-richard">Bayard</persRef>, <persRef ref="biddle-richard"
                                >Biddle</persRef>, Bodisco, <persRef ref="u">Bradley</persRef>,
                                <persRef ref="u">Bryan</persRef>—<persRef ref="carter-william"
                                >Carter</persRef>, <persRef ref="clay-henry">Clay</persRef>,
                            <persRef ref="crittenden-john">Crittenden</persRef>, <persRef ref="crogham-george">Croghan</persRef>,
                                <persRef ref="cushing-caleb">Cushing</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="fox-henry3">Fox</persRef>, <persRef ref="gales-joseph"
                                >Gales</persRef>, <persRef ref="graves-william2">Graves</persRef>,
                                <persRef ref="u">Hamilton</persRef>, <persRef ref="jenifer-daniel"
                                >Jenifer</persRef>, <persRef ref="u">Jones</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="kennedy-john">Kennedy</persRef>, <persRef ref="krehmer-george"
                                >Krehmer</persRef>, <persRef ref="legare-hugh">Legare</persRef>,
                                <persRef ref="u">Mackintosh</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="mareschal-wenzel">Marechal</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="martinez-francisco">Martinez</persRef>
                            <persRef ref="martini-adrien">Martini</persRef>, <persRef ref="u"
                                >Monmaur</persRef>, <persRef ref="nordin-gustaf">Norden</persRef>,
                                <persRef ref="u">Rives</persRef>, <persRef ref="seaton-william"
                                >Seaton</persRef>, <persRef ref="serruys-charles">Serruys</persRef>,
                                <persRef ref="tallmadge-nathaniel">Tallmadge</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="u">Thomson</persRef>, <persRef ref="watterston-george"
                                >Watterston</persRef>, <persRef ref="u">Williams</persRef>, and 3
                            others.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-19">
                    <head>19 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-19"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <p><date>19. VI.</date> Tuesday— Com<hi rend="superscript">ee.</hi> from the
                            American Society for the diffusion of useful knowledge.— <persRef
                                ref="proudfit-j">Proudfit</persRef>,</p>
                        <p><persRef ref="u">Burnap</persRef></p>

                    </div>
                </div>
                <pb n="566" type="ms"/>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-21">
                    <head>21 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-21"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="567" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>21. VI:</date> Thursday</p>
                        <p>H.R.U.S— <persRef ref="prentiss-seargent">S. S. Prentiss</persRef> offers
                            Resolutions of enquiry, and to expel <persRef ref="duncan-alexander"
                                    >Alex<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Duncan</persRef>, for a
                            publication the evening before last, in the Globe; insulting to <persRef
                                ref="stanly-edward">Stanly</persRef>
                            <persRef ref="southgate-william">Southgate</persRef>, and <persRef
                                ref="slade-william">Slade</persRef>— Debate upon it the whole day.
                            Duncan avows the publication— Motion to lay all on the table lost—
                                <persRef ref="menefee-richard">Menefee</persRef> and others reply—
                            Prentiss modifies his Resolution— <persRef ref="thompson-waddy">W.
                                Thompson</persRef> offers an Amendment— Second motion to lay on the
                            table lost— House adjourn at 7. O’Clock. Evening party at <persRef
                                ref="sewall-thomas">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                Sewall’s</persRef>— <persRef ref="u;u">Doctor and M<hi
                                    rend="superscript">rs</hi> Combe</persRef> there. <persRef
                                ref="brown-katherine">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Catherine
                                Brown</persRef>— Fancy Ball, at <persRef ref="weightman-louisa">M<hi
                                    rend="superscript">rs</hi> Weightmans</persRef></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-22">
                    <head>22 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-22"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <p><date>22. VI.</date> Friday</p>
                        <p><persRef ref="folsom-george">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> G.
                                Folsom</persRef>. N.Y. Historical Society— H.RU.S. yesterday— Com<hi
                                rend="superscript">ee.</hi> of Manufactures— No Quorum but Adams,
                                <persRef ref="naylor-charles">Naylor</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="slade-william">Slade</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="tillinghast-joseph">Tillinghast</persRef> present</p>
                        <pb n="568" type="ms"/>
                        <p>Call at the Pension-Office, with sundry Pension claims— <persRef
                                ref="gould-phebe">Phebe Gould</persRef>.</p>
                        <p>H.R.U.S. <persRef ref="petrikin-david">Petrikin</persRef> makes a short
                            Speech and moves to lay on the table the Resolution for censure upon
                                <persRef ref="duncan-alexander">A. Duncan</persRef>— Then withdraws
                            the motion for <persRef ref="elmore-franklin">Elmore</persRef> to make a
                            long Speech and renew it. Then</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-23">
                    <head>23 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-23"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor>
                        <subject>Whig Party</subject>
                        <subject>Health and Illness</subject>
                    </bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="569" type="ms"/>
                        <dateline>23. Feb<hi rend="superscript">y</hi> 1839</dateline>
                        <p><date>23. V.</date> Saturday— Call at the Pension Office; with the Letter
                            of <persRef ref="holden-oliver;holden-nehemiah">Oliver and Nehemiah
                                Holden</persRef>, and the Affidavit of<space/>Holden, to support,
                            the Pension claim of Nehemiah, and the Letter of <persRef
                                ref="packard-zibia">Zibia Packard</persRef> in favour of <persRef
                                ref="gould-phebe">Phebe Gould</persRef>— Met <persRef
                                ref="duncan-alexander">A. Duncan</persRef>, and a Pensioner—<persRef
                                ref="u">Kelly</persRef> 90 years old— H.R.U.S. Senate Bill for the
                            armed occupation of Florida— <persRef ref="robertson-john2"
                                >Robertson</persRef> moves to lay it on the table. Call of the
                            House— Motion to lay on the table lost by yeas and nays 91 to 94— Orders
                            of the day— Committee of the whole on the Union, Banks in the Chair—
                                <persRef ref="garland-james">Garland</persRef> of Virginia makes a
                            Speech of 3 hours— Independent
                            Patriotic—Self-defensive—Conservative—against the Sub-treasury and
                            against the Whigs— Followed by <persRef ref="underwood-joseph"
                                >Underwood</persRef>, full of Statistics and Political-Economy, and
                            by Halsey, pecking at petty malversations. I left the House in Session,
                            and went and dined with <persRef ref="poinsett-joel;poinsett-mary">M<hi
                                    rend="superscript">r</hi> and M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                                Poinsett</persRef>—<persRef ref="u">Barron</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="biddle-nicholas">N. Biddle</persRef>, <persRef ref="u"
                                >Bracy</persRef>, an English man <persRef ref="fox-henry3"
                                >Fox</persRef>, M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                Lo<unclear>uis?</unclear>, <persRef ref="macomb-alexander">General
                                Macomb</persRef> and <persRef ref="webster-daniel">D.
                                Webster</persRef>
                            <persRef ref="scott-winfield">General Scott</persRef> came in from the
                            North, while we were at <pb n="570" type="ms"/>Table— When I came home,
                                <persRef ref="campbell-archibald">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                Campbell</persRef>, with <persRef ref="u">Halley</persRef> and
                                <persRef ref="u">Montgomery</persRef> were here— <persRef
                                ref="adams-louisa-catherine">My wife</persRef> had been suddenly
                            seized with severe illness. <persRef ref="thomas-john7">D<hi
                                    rend="superscript">rs</hi> Thomas</persRef> and<space/>were
                            here, and she was bled, cupped and blistered— Distressed.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-24">
                    <head>24 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-24"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor>
                        <subject>Religion</subject>
                        <subject>Health and Illness</subject>
                    </bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <p><date>24. V.</date> Sunday</p>
                        <p>Heard a Stranger at the Presbyterian Church from Matthew 25.46 first part
                            of the verse— Eternity of future punishments—absurdity—and pernicious
                            tendency of both universalist creeds. <persRef ref="campbell-archibald"
                                >Campbell</persRef> dined with us. P.M. at S<hi rend="superscript"
                                >t.</hi> John’s Church. <persRef ref="doane-george">Bishop
                                Doane</persRef> read the Service for 2<hi rend="superscript">d.</hi>
                            Sunday in Lent and preached from 1. Peter 5.7.— Cast our cares upon God—
                                <persRef ref="adams-louisa-catherine">My wife</persRef> confined the
                            whole day to her bed— <persRef ref="thomas-john7">D<hi
                                    rend="superscript">r</hi> Thomas</persRef> twice here— Rumours
                            of War.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-25">
                    <head>25 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-25"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor>
                        <subject>Slavery</subject>
                        <subject>U.S. Constitution</subject>
                        <subject>Anti-Slavery Petitions to Congress</subject>
                    </bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="571" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>25. V.</date> Monday— <persRef ref="u">Anderson</persRef>, and
                                <persRef ref="u">Nelson</persRef> from Quincy, Illinois— <persRef
                                ref="thomas-john7">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Thomas</persRef>—
                            Letter from <persRef ref="lewis-charles">Lewis</persRef> and <persRef
                                ref="u">Pierce</persRef> 10. Front Street—Brooklyn—N.Y with 3
                            Letters to <persRef ref="edwards-james">J. L. Edwards</persRef>, Comm<hi
                                rend="superscript">r.</hi> of Patents</p>
                        <table>
                            <row>
                                <cell>1.</cell>
                                <cell>With Declaration and application of</cell>
                                <cell><persRef ref="steenburgh-simon">Simon
                                    Steenburgh</persRef></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>2.</cell>
                                <cell/>
                                <cell><persRef ref="williams-william2">William
                                    Williams</persRef></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>3.</cell>
                                <cell/>
                                <cell><persRef ref="duffield-margaretta">Margaretta
                                        Duffield</persRef>.</cell>
                            </row>
                        </table>
                        <p>Left at the Pension Office</p>
                        <p>H.R.U.S. Resolution day— <persRef ref="cambreleng-churchill"
                                >Cambreleng</persRef> moves to suspend the Rules to receive Reports
                            of Committees— I asked leave to offer 3. Resolutions for Amendments to
                            the Constitution, to abolish Slavery, and a Petition of <persRef
                                ref="jay-john4">John Jay</persRef> and 43 citizens of New-York; but
                            the question was put on Cambreleng’s motion, the rules were
                            suspended—the Committees reported; and the House went into Committee of
                            the whole on the Union on the civil and diplomatic appropriation Bill—
                                <persRef ref="slade-william">Slade</persRef>— Hayti— <persRef
                                ref="ogle-charles">Ogle</persRef>—the branch mints— No Quorum—
                            Committee finally rise— Adjourned at 1. A.M.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-26">
                    <head>26 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-26"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor></bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="572" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>26. VII.</date> Tuesday— H.R.U.S. Com<hi rend="superscript"
                                >ee.</hi> of the whole on the Union Banks in the Chair. The Civil
                            and diplomatic appropriation Bill— <persRef ref="graham-james4"
                                >Graham</persRef> of N.C. <persRef ref="dawson-william"
                                >Dawson</persRef> and <persRef ref="bynum-jesse">Bynum</persRef>
                            reply to <persRef ref="ogle-charles">Ogle</persRef>; also <persRef
                                ref="mercer-charles">C. F. Mercer</persRef>— Message from <persRef
                                ref="vanburen-martin">P.U.S.</persRef> on the North-eastern
                            boundary— Message and documents <persRef ref="howard-benjamin"
                                >Howard</persRef>, <persRef ref="thompson-waddy">Waddy
                                Thompson</persRef>
                            <persRef ref="evans-george2">Evans</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="petrikin-david">Pretikin</persRef> moves the previous question,
                            withdraws it J. Q. A—<persRef ref="lincoln-levi2">Lincoln</persRef>, <persRef ref="cushing-caleb">Cushing</persRef>, <persRef ref="pickens-francis">Pickens</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="sergeant-john">J. Sergeant</persRef>, <persRef
                                ref="everett-horace">Everett</persRef> previous Question. Message
                            referred to Com<hi rend="superscript">ee.</hi> of Foreign Affairs with
                            permission to sit during the sitting of the House Motions to print extra
                            copies. <persRef ref="harlan-james">Harlan</persRef> moves to suspend
                            the rules to present the <persRef ref="swartwout-samuel"
                                >Swartwout</persRef> defalcation Committee 81 to 56 not two thirds.
                            Committee of the whole on the Union again— Ogle repeats his speech on
                            the Branch Mints— Bynum snarls a reply The Bill reported to the House—at
                            10. P.M. Harlan presents the defalcation Committee’s report— Postponed
                            till to-morrow morning— Home at 11. P.M.</p>

                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-27">
                    <head>27 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-27"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor>
                        <subject>Native Americans</subject>
                    </bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="573" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>27. VII.</date> Wednesday— H.R.U.S. Harlan presents the report of
                            the <persRef ref="swartwout-samuel">Swartwout</persRef> and <persRef
                                ref="price-william2">Price</persRef> defalcation <persRef
                                ref="owens-george">Com<hi rend="superscript">ee.</hi>
                                Owens</persRef> presents the Minority Report— <persRef
                                ref="petrikin-david">Petrikin</persRef> demands the reading of the
                            whole; but compounds for a bargain no part of them should be read. 20000
                            copies of the report and 5000 copies of the Journal to be printed.
                                <persRef ref="hall-hiland">Hiland</persRef> Hall presents a report
                            from a select Committee against Virginia comutation claims— All Virginia
                            in a flame Motion to print postponed— Civil and diplomatic expenditure
                            Bill passed to the 3<hi rend="superscript">d.</hi> reading and passed.
                            Motion to meet for the rest of the Session at 10 A.M. Daily. and to take
                            a recess from 3 to 1/2 past 4. 3. Messages from <persRef
                                ref="vanburen-martin">P.U.S</persRef> Memorandum between <persRef
                                ref="forsyth-john">J. Forsyth</persRef>, and <persRef
                                ref="fox-henry3">H. S. Fox</persRef>—to pacify the fray between
                            Maine and New-Brunswick— Bill of Appropriations to suppress Indian
                            hostilities in Florida.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div type="entry" xml:id="jqadiaries-v50-1839-02-28">
                    <head>28 February 1839</head>
                    <bibl><author>JQA</author><date type="creation" when="1839-02-28"/><editor
                            role="transcription">Neal Millikan</editor>
                        <subject>Native Americans</subject>
                    </bibl>
                    <div type="docbody">
                        <pb n="574" type="ms"/>
                        <p><date>28. VII.</date> Thursday—</p>
                        <p><persRef ref="u">Gerstner</persRef> with a Letter from <persRef
                                ref="quincy-josiah2">President Quincy</persRef>. Austrian undertaker
                            of Railroads—Russia. England— <persRef ref="dearborn-henry2"
                                >Dearborns</persRef> Letters— Alabama and Georgia Railroad—</p>
                        <p>H.R.U.S.— <persRef ref="hall-hiland">Hiland Hall’s</persRef> Report, read
                            till the expiration of the Morning hour.— Report and Bill of the
                            Committee of foreign Affairs— I proposed a slight amendment to the
                            report—debate thereon— My amendment adopted: 10,000 copies of the
                            message, documents, report and bill to be printed under the direction of
                            the Com<hi rend="superscript">ee.</hi> Bill to suppress indian
                            hostilities passed</p>
                        <p>Recess— Draught of Report from Committee of Manufactures— <persRef
                                ref="morris-samuel">Samuel W. Morris</persRef> of the Com<hi
                                rend="superscript">ee.</hi> of Accounts Investigating Committee’s
                            tavern Bills contested Com<hi rend="superscript">ee.</hi> of the Whole—
                                <persRef ref="mckennan-thomas">M’Kennan</persRef> Chairman. Bill to
                            take the 6<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> Census— <persRef
                                ref="garland-rice">Rice Garland</persRef>— Bill passed</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
